overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application to ensure all acceptance criteria were met. The agent performed a
  detailed analysis, identifying several critical missing features.
  Subsequently, the agent proceeded to implement these features, including a
  1-10 severity scale for tiredness with safety warnings, detection and tailored
  recommendations for COMISA and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, and the
  integration of placeholder outbound links to relevant sleep and mental health
  resources. Additionally, a weighted scoring system for Excessive Daytime
  Sleepiness was implemented to provide more accurate assessments. The changes
  were applied across the application, affecting data types, validation, the
  interactive questionnaire UI, and both the on-screen and PDF generated
  reports, ensuring a more robust and informative user experience.
